  "texts": [
    "In the current study, the formula used is based on the Log OR, with an addition of 0.5 to each cell in a 2 × 2 contingency table.",
    "This adjustment, known as the Haldane Anscombe correction, addresses the issue of zero.",
    "Without this correction, an OR is involving a zero count would be undefined due to division by zero.",
    "Given that some terms in the generated data have zero counts in one corpus or another, applying an appropriate correction method is essential.",
    "The formula is used in this study: OR = log((O11 + 0.5) × (O22 + 0.5) (O12 + 0.5) × (O21 + 0.5))"
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}